To simplify the left side of the equation, we can find a common denominator:  \begin{align*}
\frac{1}{x-1} + \frac{2x}{x - 1} &= \frac{(x-1) + 2x}{x-1} \\
&= \frac{x}{x-1}
\end{align*}So the equation is  $\frac{x}{x-1} = 5$.  Multiplying both sides by $x-1$ gives  $x = 5(x - 1)$. Expanding the right side gives  $x = 5x - 5$.  Subtracting $x$ from both sides  yields $-x = -5$.  Finally, multiplying both sides by $-1$ gives  $x = \boxed{5}$.
